-- Aurora Gold Mine Guards Arrested After Illegal Miner Killed Amid Skirmish
-- Ron Derby
-- 2010-09-20T07:15:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/aurora-gold-mine-guards-arrested-after-illegal-miner-killed-amid-skirmish.html

          
          
             South African police arrested four
security guards working at a gold mine partly owned by Nelson
Mandela’s grandson and President Jacob Zuma’s nephew, on charges
of murder, attempted murder and assault, police spokesman Eugene
Opperman said.  
 The victims were allegedly illegal miners and were
operating at Aurora’s Grootvlei mine east of Johannesburg, he
said by mobile phone today.  
 Michael Hulley, a lawyer for Aurora, didn’t immediately
respond to a message left on his mobile phone seeking comment.  
 S.African Police says guards arrested on charges of murder,
attempted murder and assault  
